<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="238" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1038,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1038,1063]" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Males of this species are easily distinguished from its congeners by the wide, ventrally expanded conductor, occupying almost half of the tegulum (
<figureCitation box="[758,834,1074,1099]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1919,1941]" captionTargetBox="[165,1420,605,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,600,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Cryptodrassus helvolus (O. P. Cambridge, 1872). 1. Male left palp, ventral view. 2. Same, retrolateral view. 3. Same, prolateral view. 4. Same, dorsal view. 5. Epigyne. 6. Vulva. Co: conductor. Arrows show the two chambers of spermathecae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002544/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Figs 1</figureCitation>
̄3) and by the retrolateral tibial apophysis, being forwardly directed (
<figureCitation box="[381,490,1110,1135]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1919,1941]" captionTargetBox="[165,1420,605,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,600,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Cryptodrassus helvolus (O. P. Cambridge, 1872). 1. Male left palp, ventral view. 2. Same, retrolateral view. 3. Same, prolateral view. 4. Same, dorsal view. 5. Epigyne. 6. Vulva. Co: conductor. Arrows show the two chambers of spermathecae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002544/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Figs 2, 4</figureCitation>
). Females are distinguished by the rounded median cavity and the absence of an anterior hood (
<figureCitation box="[325,397,1146,1171]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1919,1941]" captionTargetBox="[165,1420,605,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,600,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Cryptodrassus helvolus (O. P. Cambridge, 1872). 1. Male left palp, ventral view. 2. Same, retrolateral view. 3. Same, prolateral view. 4. Same, dorsal view. 5. Epigyne. 6. Vulva. Co: conductor. Arrows show the two chambers of spermathecae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002544/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), present in both 
<taxonomicName authority="Chatzaki, 2002" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" box="[611,921,1146,1171]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis box="[611,736,1147,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. creticus</emphasis>
Chatzaki, 2002
</taxonomicName>
(Chatzaki 
<emphasis box="[1052,1113,1147,1171]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">et al.</emphasis>
, 2002, Figs 61̄62) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Balogh, 1935)" authorityName="Balogh" authorityYear="1935" baseAuthorityName="Balogh" baseAuthorityYear="1935" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Cryptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hungaricus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="238">C. hungaricus</emphasis>
(Balogh, 1935)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy" box="[468,716,1182,1207]" pageId="1" pageNumber="238" refString="Murphy, J. (2007) Gnaphosid genera of the world. Uol. 1 &amp; 2. British Arachnological Society, St Neots, Cambridgeshire, 605 pp. [pp. i ‾ xii, 1 ‾ 92 &amp; i ‾ ii, 93 ‾ 605]" type="book" year="2007" yearSuffix="p">Murphy, 2007, p. 529</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
